"n.空中秋千 【英】 n. 空中吊杠，高秋千(a short bar banging high above the ground from two ropes used by gymnasts and acrobats) n. 空中秋千(用于体育锻炼或杂技表演) 【记】tr = tran转, ape猩猩, ze: 猩猩在秋千上转来转去. 【记】trap+ 音：贼，陷肼抓贼，电视里经常看到设个陷井抓贼，他一踩到那个网上就被吊在空中挂在树上吊秋千；trapezium 梯形 trapeze (n.)  swing with a cross-bar, used for feats of strength and agility, 1861, from French trapèze, from Late Latin trapezium (see trapezium), probably because the crossbar, the ropes and the ceiling formed a trapezium. The French, to whose powers of invention (so long as you do not insist upon utility) there is no limit, have invented for the world the Trapeze .... [""Chambers's Journal,"" July 6, 1861]"
